Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read what you can and cannot do

EgyptAir is operating flights from Cairo to London on Sunday 10 May and Tuesday 12 May. Both flights are now open for bookings by calling the EgyptAir reservations office:
From an Egyptian landline: 0900 70000
From an Egyptian mobile: 1717
From an international line +971 4 435 8444
Bookings can also be made in person at any EgyptAir office in Cairo from 10:00am – 2:00pm daily.
Lufthansa is operating a flight from Cairo to Frankfurt on Monday, 11 May. Bookings can be made by calling the Lufthansa Sales Office in Egypt on 02 258 03500 between 8:30am – 3:00pm Sunday – Thursday. Passengers will be required to wear face masks onboard. Options for onward travel to the UK might be limited: please make sure you have arrangements in place before booking.
Scheduled flights into and out of the country are suspended.
This advice will continue to be updated with the latest information on returning to the UK.
If you have questions about visa requirements to enter the UK, please visit the GOV.UK website.
British nationals in Egypt should continue to regularly check this travel advice, and follow the instructions of the local authorities.
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the Embassy on 02 2791 6000.
You can also follow the British Embassy in Cairo on Facebook and on Twitter.
You will need to pay for your return travel to the UK. If departure options are available but you cannot afford the travel costs and have exhausted all other options for getting funds, you may be eligible to apply for an emergency loan from the government. This is a last resort option and you would need to repay the loan when you are back in the UK. For more information, you should contact Corporate Travel Management (CTM). CTM are a commercial partner of the FCO and are authorised to administer such loans on behalf of the FCO.
See more information and advice about staying where you are if you cannot return to the UK.
Your journey home
The National Travel Health Network and Centre (NaTHNaC) provides advice on how to stay safe as you travel by air.
When you arrive back in the UK, follow the guidance for when you return to the UK on steps you should take to protect yourself and others.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
